To create four new buttons with different background colors using inline button syntax, you can use the following HTML code:

```html
<button class="btn btn-xs" id="btnRed" name="btnRed" style="background-color: red;">
    Red Button
</button>
<button class="btn btn-xs" id="btnBlue" name="btnBlue" style="background-color: blue;">
    Blue Button
</button>
<button class="btn btn-xs" id="btnBrown" name="btnBrown" style="background-color: brown;">
    Brown Button
</button>
<button class="btn btn-xs" id="btnPink" name="btnPink" style="background-color: pink;">
    Pink Button
</button>
<button class="btn btn-xs" id="btnOrange" name="btnOrange" style="background-color: orange;">
    Orange Button
</button>
```

This code creates buttons with the specified background colors using inline styles. You can adjust the text and other attributes as needed.